  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18-79 years of age

          -  Patients who failed the topical and oral antibiotics after 6 month therapy.

          -  Patients who failed the topical retinoids after 6 month therapy.

          -  Patients that are not good candidate to start oral isotretinoin (Accutane) due to
             contraindications.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who have had Isotretinoin therapy less that 1 year prior to this ALA-PDT
             procedure.

          -  Patients who have an adverse reaction to light exposure (for example photo-
             exacerbated seizures).

          -  Patients with a history of porphyria.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
